records.addlTxt:
1:46 PM; Case called for Plea/sentencing hearing. Prosecuting attorney Andrew Nesheim in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Matthew L Brennecke in court.  Attorney J Andrew Herbers Jr. in court for Matthew L Brennecke.  Court notes a plea questionnaire has been filed and inquires how the matter is proceeding.  Atty. Herbers confirms his client is prepared to proceed today.  State recites the offer.  Atty. Herbers confirms the offer.  Court conducts plea colloquy with the defendant.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1, 2 & 3, Court finds defendant guilty of Counts 1, 2 & 3.  Court orders Counts 4 & 5 dismissed and read in.

Sentencing arguments made by the State.
Sentencing arguments made by Atty. Herbers.
Defendant presents statements.

COUNT 1: 
The Court Orders the Following:

Withheld sentence

Term of Probation: 1 Year & 6 Months

Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
-	Follow any conditions deemed appropriate by Agent;
-	No contact with any Kwik Trip store in Waukesha County.
-	Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
-	Take Thinking for a Change Course;
-	Perform 20 hours of community service.

COSTS:  $253.00 (includes DRGOD surcharge);

DNA Surcharge: $200.00;

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of probation. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.


